#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.35:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Dānavagga "
msgstr "4. Giving "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an8.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Dānūpapattisutta "
msgstr "35. Rebirth by Giving "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an8.35:1.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhimā, bhikkhave, dānūpapattiyo. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these eight rebirths by giving. "

msgctxt "an8.35:1.2"
msgid "Katamā aṭṭha? "
msgstr "What eight? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.35:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "First, someone gives to ascetics or brahmins such things as food, drink, clothing, vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; and bed, house, and lighting. "

#. VAR: paccāsīsati → paccāsiṃsati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.35:1.4"
msgid "So yaṃ deti taṃ paccāsīsati. "
msgstr "Whatever they give, they expect something back. "

msgctxt "an8.35:1.5"
msgid "So passati khattiyamahāsāle vā brāhmaṇamahāsāle vā gahapatimahāsāle vā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappite samaṅgībhūte paricārayamāne. "
msgstr "They see a well-to-do aristocrat or brahmin or householder amusing themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "an8.35:1.6"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "It occurs to them: "

msgctxt "an8.35:1.7"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders!’ "

msgctxt "an8.35:1.8"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "They settle on that idea, concentrate on it and develop it. "

#. VAR: hīne vimuttaṃ → hīnedhimuttaṃ (s1-3, pts1) | vimuttanti vā vissaṭṭhaṃ (ṭīkāsaṃvaṇṇanā)
#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.35:1.9"
msgid "Tassa taṃ cittaṃ hīne vimuttaṃ, uttari abhāvitaṃ, tatrūpapattiyā saṃvattati. "
msgstr "As they’ve settled for less and not developed further, their idea leads to rebirth there. "

msgctxt "an8.35:1.10"
msgid "Kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders. "

msgctxt "an8.35:1.11"
msgid "Tañca kho sīlavato vadāmi, no dussīlassa. "
msgstr "But I say that this is only for those of ethical conduct, not for the unethical. "

msgctxt "an8.35:1.12"
msgid "Ijjhati, bhikkhave, sīlavato cetopaṇidhi visuddhattā. (1) "
msgstr "The heart’s wish of an ethical person succeeds because of their purity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.240, sc2
msgctxt "an8.35:2.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "Next, someone gives to ascetics or brahmins … "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.2"
msgid "So yaṃ deti taṃ paccāsīsati. "
msgstr "Whatever they give, they expect something back. "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.3"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And they’ve heard: "

#. VAR: cātumahārājikā → cātummahārājikā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.35:2.4"
msgid "‘cātumahārājikā devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The Gods of the Four Great Kings are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’ "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "It occurs to them: "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.6"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the Gods of the Four Great Kings!’ … "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.7"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.8"
msgid "Tassa taṃ cittaṃ hīne vimuttaṃ, uttari abhāvitaṃ, tatrūpapattiyā saṃvattati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.9"
msgid "Kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the Gods of the Four Great Kings. "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.10"
msgid "Tañca kho sīlavato vadāmi, no dussīlassa. "
msgstr "But I say that this is only for those of ethical conduct, not for the unethical. "

msgctxt "an8.35:2.11"
msgid "Ijjhati, bhikkhave, sīlavato cetopaṇidhi visuddhattā. (2) "
msgstr "The heart’s wish of an ethical person succeeds because of their purity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an8.35:3.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "Next, someone gives to ascetics or brahmins … "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.2"
msgid "So yaṃ deti taṃ paccāsīsati. "
msgstr "Whatever they give, they expect something back. "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.3"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "And they’ve heard: "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.4"
msgid "tāvatiṃsā devā … pe … "
msgstr "‘The Gods of the Thirty-Three …’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.35:3.5"
msgid "yāmā devā … "
msgstr "‘The Gods of Yama …’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.35:3.6"
msgid "tusitā devā … "
msgstr "‘The Joyful Gods …’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.35:3.7"
msgid "nimmānaratī devā … "
msgstr "‘The Gods Who Love to Create …’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.35:3.8"
msgid "paranimmitavasavattī devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulāti. "
msgstr "‘The Gods Who Control the Creations of Others are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’ "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.9"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "It occurs to them: "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.10"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others!’ "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.11"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "They settle on that idea, concentrate on it and develop it. "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.12"
msgid "Tassa taṃ cittaṃ hīne vimuttaṃ, uttari abhāvitaṃ, tatrūpapattiyā saṃvattati. "
msgstr "As they’ve settled for less and not developed further, their idea leads to rebirth there. "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.13"
msgid "Kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others. "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.14"
msgid "Tañca kho sīlavato vadāmi, no dussīlassa. "
msgstr "But I say that this is only for those of ethical conduct, not for the unethical. "

msgctxt "an8.35:3.15"
msgid "Ijjhati, bhikkhave, sīlavato cetopaṇidhi visuddhattā. (3–7.) "
msgstr "The heart’s wish of an ethical person succeeds because of their purity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.241, sc4
msgctxt "an8.35:4.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "Next, someone gives to ascetics or brahmins such things as food, drink, clothing, vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; and bed, house, and lighting. "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.2"
msgid "So yaṃ deti taṃ paccāsīsati. "
msgstr "Whatever they give, they expect something back. "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.3"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And they’ve heard: "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.4"
msgid "‘brahmakāyikā devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The Gods of Brahmā’s Host are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’ "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "It occurs to them: "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.6"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the Gods of Brahmā’s Host!’ "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.7"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "They settle on that idea, concentrate on it and develop it. "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.8"
msgid "Tassa taṃ cittaṃ hīne vimuttaṃ, uttari abhāvitaṃ, tatrūpapattiyā saṃvattati. "
msgstr "As they’ve settled for less and not developed further, their idea leads to rebirth there. "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.9"
msgid "Kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the Gods of Brahmā’s Host. "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.10"
msgid "Tañca kho sīlavato vadāmi, no dussīlassa; "
msgstr "But I say that this is only for those of ethical conduct, not for the unethical. "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.11"
msgid "vītarāgassa, no sarāgassa. "
msgstr "And for those free of desire, not those with desire. "

msgctxt "an8.35:4.12"
msgid "Ijjhati, bhikkhave, sīlavato cetopaṇidhi vītarāgattā. "
msgstr "The heart’s wish of an ethical person succeeds because of their freedom from desire. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.35:4.13"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha dānūpapattiyo”ti. (8) "
msgstr "These are the eight rebirths by giving.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.35:4.14"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

